# Commit Message Rules (Cursor MDC)

把閱讀者當作剛接觸專案的高中生, 減少使用專業術語, 清楚的寫下commit message。

## 語言(強制)

-   盡量使用繁體中文, 除非是英文專有名詞或技術術語或類別, 方法名稱, 變數名稱...。

## Format
<type>(<scope>): <subject>

## Types
feat      -> new feature
fix       -> bug fix
refactor  -> code restructure (no behavior change)
perf      -> performance improvement
test      -> test changes
docs      -> documentation only
chore     -> tooling / build / config
data      -> data-driven changes (game configs, tables)
sim       -> deterministic simulation logic changes

## Scope (required when possible)
combat, damage, buff, proc, tag, ai, skill, ui, inventory, save, sim, data

## Subject Rules
- Use present tense (add, fix, change)
- No period at end
- Keep under ~72 chars
- Be specific and searchable

## Body (optional but recommended)
- Explain WHY not just WHAT
- List key changes
- Mention deterministic impact if relevant

## Breaking Change
Use:
BREAKING CHANGE: <description>

or footer style in body.

## Examples

feat(combat): add critical hit calculation
fix(sim): remove frame-dependent randomness
refactor(buff): simplify stacking logic

feat(ai): add kiting behavior

BREAKING CHANGE: AI state machine updated

## Rules for game systems (Unity Roguelike)
- All sim changes must be deterministic
- Avoid frame-dependent logic in sim layer
- Data-driven changes should use `data` scope


